  • PRIMARY axis = `emopaper_regen__valence_pooled__mean__pc0__unit`, layer L27, aggregate `mean`
    (the Seg-10 pre-registered, Seg-6-self-report-INDEPENDENT pick → CLEAN test target).
  • COMMENSURABILITY RULE: project the Seg-6 `mean` aggregate onto the `mean`-built direction, `median`→`median`,
    at the SAME layer. (The `eot`/`last` POSITION comparison keeps the direction fixed at the validated
    `mean`/pc0 vector and only varies the Seg-6 READ POSITION — there is no eot/last-built validated direction;
    this is the Seg-5 convention and is documented as a position comparison, not a same-aggregate read.)
  • PRIMARY statistical unit = per-task MEAN over R=3 responses (n=208 independent). Response-level grain
    (n=624) kept for reliability (ICC) + a robustness view.
  • The axis is a relative RANKER (path-dependent neutral offset) → use rank/correlation, never absolute
    projection thresholds.
